26/01/2007
PARIS, France -- Turkey and Greece were among the countries that pledged to assist Lebanon's reconstruction, during an international donor conference in Paris on Thursday (January 25th). According to separate reports from Ankara and Athens, Turkey vowed assistance of 20m euros, while Greece committed to providing 5m euros in aid. In all, donors pledged 7.6 billion euros to the rebuilding effort. (Zaman, NTV, ANA-MPA - 25/01/07)
